
sample_aes_cmac: Generate AES-CMAC of the data requested with
                 some hardcoded key in the container

Input required AES-CMAC operation:
- Key (hardcoded in container)
- Message
- Message length (length calculated based input data message )

To run (load and start) container:
$ mwtest.py -c100 run sample_aes_cmac.img

To send data to container:
$ printf 'Do AES-CMAC operation' > testfile
$ cmtest data -f100 testfile

The test messages below are from rfc4493.
Refer https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4493#section-4 for more info.

Test message 1:
$ perl -e 'print pack("H*", @ARGV)' "6bc1bee22e409f96e93d7e117393172a" > testfile16
$ cmtest data -f100 testfile16
Expected MAC: 070a16b46b4d4144f79bdd9dd04a287c

Test message 2:
$ perl -e 'print pack("H*", @ARGV)' "6bc1bee22e409f96e93d7e117393172aae2d8a571e03ac9c9eb76fac45af8e5130c81c46a35ce411" > testfile40
$ cmtest data -f100 testfile40
Expected MAC: dfa66747de9ae63030ca32611497c827

Test message 3:
$ perl -e 'print pack("H*", @ARGV)' "6bc1bee22e409f96e93d7e117393172aae2d8a571e03ac9c9eb76fac45af8e5130c81c46a35ce411e5fbc1191a0a52eff69f2445df4f9b17ad2b417be66c3710" > testfile64
$ cmtest data -f100 testfile64
Expected CMAC: 51f0bebf7e3b9d92fc49741779363cfe

To unload container:
$ mwtest.py -c100 unload
